A C O N C U R R E N T R E S O L U T I O N
To urge Congress to reissue Department of Defense 1
Civilian Retiree Identification Cards. 2
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE STATE OF OHIO (THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING):
WHEREAS, In February 2023, the United States Department of 3
Defense, pursuant to the federal REAL ID Act, stopped issuing 4
new Civilian Retiree Identification Cards and no longer renews 5
existing cards; and 6
WHEREAS, Civilian Retiree Identification Cards allowed 7
retired civilian Department of Defense personnel to easily 8
access military recreational areas such as Wright-Patterson Air 9
Force Base FamCamp and other camps, parks, and historic sites; 10
and 11
WHEREAS, In order to access these sites, civilian retirees 12
must now request access from the installation commander and 13
present a REAL ID Act-compliant driver's license and retirement 14
documentation; and 15

